# .dockerignore
# ─────────────
# Tells Docker which files to EXCLUDE from the build context.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#
# When you run "docker build .", Docker packages every file in the
# current directory into a "build context" and sends it to the Docker
# daemon before processing the Dockerfile. Without a .dockerignore,
# this project would include:
#   - ~700 MB of training checkpoints (checkpoint-500, checkpoint-750)
#   - ~50 MB of Python __pycache__ directories
#   - The .git directory (~5 MB of object history)
#   - Your .env file (SECURITY RISK — this has your API key)
#
# A tight .dockerignore keeps the build context small (fast uploads
# to remote Docker daemons) and, crucially, keeps secrets out of the image.

# ── Secrets — NEVER bake these into a Docker image ───────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example    # .env.example is safe to include (it has no real values)

# ── Git ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ── Python cache — these get regenerated inside the container anyway ──────────
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
*.egg-info
dist/
build/
.eggs/

# ── Virtual environments ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/
.env/

# ── Training checkpoints — large and not needed at inference time ─────────────
# The adapter/ directory IS included (see Dockerfile COPY command).
# The checkpoint directories are NOT — each is ~400 MB.
models/finetuned/distilbert-lora/checkpoint-*/

# ── Raw training data — not needed to run the API ────────────────────────────
data/raw/
data/generator/

# ── Evaluation results — generated outputs, not source ───────────────────────
eval/results/

# ── Test files — not needed in production image ──────────────────────────────
tests/

# ── IDE and OS files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Logs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
debug.log

# ── Node (for the report generator script — not part of the API) ─────────────
node_modules/
generate_report.js
